The Osun Commandant of the Nigerian Security and Civil Defence Corps (NSCDC), Sunday Agboola has reiterated the Command’s readiness to combat crime in the State. The Osun NSCDC Commandant made this known during an interview with journalists in Osogbo on Wednesday. Agboola, while appreciating the good citizens of the State for their support to the success of the gubernatorial election, assured that the Command was ready to guarantee adequate security. “I want to assure the people of Osun State of adequate security after the just concluded gubernatorial election. The Command is gallantry ready to carry out its mandate and excellent security service delivery. “I also assure the citizens of the State of professionalism and civility in the discharge of the duties the Corps is constitutionally saddled with,” he said. Agboola also enjoined the residents of the State to provide the Command with information to help provide adequate security in all nooks and crannies of Osun State.